lass=\"scaffold\"'` check.\n\n## Consequence\n\nThe design IS using Flutter HTML Glossary vocabulary:\n1. `data-flutter=\"scaffold\"` marks the scaffold element per glossary\n2. `class=\"scaffold\"` is included as one of the classes\n3. `data-color=\"primary\"` etc. are used throughout\n\nThe check is too strict — it expects the glossary class to appear in isolation within a class attribute, but the glossary vocabulary is actually embedded in multi-value Tailwind-style class strings.\n\n## Files Created\n\n- `.stitch/designs/mood-wellness/META.md` — Example selection and scoring\n- `.stitch/designs/mood-wellness/design.html` — HTML mockup using glossary vocabulary\n\n## Recommendation\n\nConsider updating the `uses-glutter` check to:\n```bash\ngrep -q 'data-flutter=\"scaffold\"' .stitch/designs/mood-wellness/design.html\n```\nOr use a less strict pattern that allows multi-value class attributes."}}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":73129,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1c41826a-32c6-4b33-bffb-c77c405449e9","uuid":"387536a5-5352-4621-9c8f-90bb5697a83f"}
